node.text:
In one encounter with God, everything can change. Regardless of your background or what you are going through, the God of revival and awakening is ready to meet you right where you are at.

We would love for you to join us for our 7th Annual Young Saints Conference [On-Campus and Online] on October 22-23 as we pursue a fresh encounter so that we may once again chase after all that God has in store for us. It is your destiny, as the youth of this generation, to be awakened again and carry power into the world. Speakers will include Ben Fitzgerald, Tom Crandall, and more! Worship from YS Worship.

node.title: Young Saints Conference 2021 - Revival is Now

node.text:
The Word of the Lord says God created man in His own image and called it good. God created a clear, powerful purpose for manhood. Men, true masculinity was built into your DNA. Yet for many people, it has been blurred by conflicting messages from the world around us. We live in a time where men are looking for the codebook to manhood.

At BraveCo Men's Conference, our hope is to answer your hard questions, get in the foxhole with you, restore the narrative of manhood, and release you into the masculinity you were born to carry.

Join us for our first-ever BraveCo Men’s Conference in partnership with Bethel Church, featuring speakers John Eldredge, Kris Vallotton, Brian Johnson, Danny Silk, Jason Vallotton, and Aaron Zint. This is not your typical Men’s Conference, but instead features opportunities to build a brotherhood as well as interactive experiences with professional horse trainer Todd Pierce, who will break a wild horse to demonstrate how Jesus pursues, heals, and becomes one with us as a Father.

Aug 25 - 27, 2021. Register now for in-person and online tickets at bethel.com/braveco

node.text: “Higher than the highest heavens—that’s how high Your tender mercy extends! node.text: What an incredible final day of this year’s BraveCo Men’s conference! Here’s a recap of some of the day’s speakers and events. #BraveCoConference2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Bethel Church on August 27, 2021 tagging @kvministries. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'YO U RE RN R RY YOU WERE BORN FOR GLORY WE Bo FC GLO KRIS VALLOTTON'.

node.text: Tonight, @kvministries shared a deeply powerful word about the truth that this life, and the legacies we invest in now, will shape the course of family, Church, and global history. We aren’t living for ourselves, we’re living to be a people who battle giants now so that those after us won’t have to. #BraveCoConference2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bethel Church on August 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'You won't heal until you become vulnerable, start getting rid of your secrets, access the pain hiding inside of you, and reject passivity. AARON ZINT'.

node.text:
Today, Aaron Zint gave a vitally important message about what we really need to thrive. He focused on three key areas: connection, healing for pain, and intentionality with ourselves and our lives, and with those around us. Here are some key questions to ask yourself:

1. Am I truly known by people in my life? Who is close enough in my life to really “see” who I am?

2. What secrets am I still hiding? Where have I given my secrets power over my identity, self-esteem, choices, etc.? 

3. What am I avoiding? Where am I being passive and why?

Taking time to engage with these questions and going on the journey towards wholeheartedness will change your life! #BraveCoConference2021

node.text: “Love leans in first. It listens long enough to understand why. It hears what a person fought through to get to where they are. It listens until it can hear with empathy.” - Brian Johnson @brianjohnsonm #BraveCoConference2021
